<h2>Stiffness or decreased movement, Unable to grip (hands) and Weakness</h2>
<p>WebMD Symptom Checker helps you find the most common medical conditions indicated by the symptoms stiffness or decreased movement, unable to grip (hands) and weakness including Osteoarthritis, Multiple sclerosis, and Brachial plexus nerve injury.</p>
<p>There  are 13 conditions  associated with stiffness or decreased movement, unable to grip (hands) and weakness. The links below will provide you with more detailed information on these medical conditions from the WebMD Symptom Checker and help provide a better understanding of causes and treatment of these related conditions.</p>
</div>
